  <Subject Subject_ID="300025764">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300168457</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>people in religion [300168457], people in religion and related occupations [300025746], people in the humanities [300025485], people by occupation [300024980], people (agents) [300024979], People (hierarchy name) [300024978], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Those who are sent on or engaged in religious work outside of their countries of origin. Missionary work is usually undertaken to convince others to join a religion or to assist impoverished or sick people.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093853/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mensen die worden of zijn uitgezonden om religieus werk te doen buiten hun eigen land. De bedoeling van missionariswerk is gewoonlijk om anderen te overtuigen een religie aan te nemen, of om armen en zieken bij te staan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Solche, die gesandt oder beauftragt werden, um religiösen Tätigkeiten außerhalb ihrer Herkunftsländer nachzugehen. Missionsarbeit besteht gewöhnlich darin, andere davon zu überzeugen, einer Religion beizutreten oder Armen und Kranken zu helfen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
